# Business Domain (BA)

## Product

ChatCRM is **vertical-agnostic** — cocok untuk bisnis apa saja yang punya customer, transaksi, dan tim CS (WhatsApp). Owner menyesuaikan nama layanan, kategori, tag, dan status order. Currency: **IDR** via `formatRupiah()`. Dates: Indonesian labels via `formatDate()`.

## RFM segments

| Segment | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| champions | High R+F+M — best customers |
| loyal | High frequency & value |
| promising | Recent but low frequency |
| at_risk | Was active, recency dropping |
| new | First/recent single purchase |
| dormant | Long inactive |

Scoring lives in `lib/rfm.ts` — do not change thresholds without updating seed data expectations and dashboard copy.

## Cadence

- Labels: `harian`, `mingguan`, `dua_mingguan`, `bulanan`, `tidak_tentu`
- Display via `CADENCE_LABEL_TEXT`
- `cadenceFor(purchases, cadenceOverrideDays)` — override set per customer in store
- Cadence follow-up ≠ RFM at-risk — dashboard treats them separately; preserve that distinction

## CLV

Simple projection in `lib/clv.ts`: avg order × frequency/month × 12. Used for supervisor ranking, not shown to CS unless permission added.

## Customer model

Key fields: `purchases[]`, `assignedAgentId`, `conversationStatus`, `orderStatus`, `priority`, `tags`, `conversationTags`, `segmentHistory`, `manualShares`, `cadenceOverrideDays`.

Order status values: `dalam_proses`, `siap_diambil`, `selesai`.

## Seed data

- Add customers in `data/customers.ts` with realistic purchase timelines relative to `isoDaysAgo()`.
- Messages in `data/conversations.ts` — customer sends use `senderId: customer.id`.
- Keep agent IDs consistent: `rina`, `budi`, `sari`, `admin`, `hartono`.

## BA rules for new features

- Every customer-facing label needs Indonesian copy consistent with existing screens.
- New metrics must define which roles see them (CS vs supervisor vs owner).
- If a field is sensitive, add to `FieldVisibilityRule` — not ad-hoc hiding in one component.
